  "doc_id": "45866",
  "text": ". The incidence of HD in different populations around the world varied with epidemiological reports finding between 0.42 to 17.2 cases per 100 000 [CITATION_1] . Clinical diagnosis of motor onset typically occurs in the prime of adult life, and symptoms progress inexorably, leading to chronic deterioration of patient health. The median timeframe from the manifestation of motor function symptoms to patient death is approximately 18 years [CITATION_2] . No cures are currently available.",
